 :tx/rationale "FAILURE MODE DIAGNOSIS: Why braid observe failed to surface ACP-related specs/tasks when creating TSV and CTP observations. Root cause: knowledge_relevance_scan() in guidance.rs uses keyword_alignment_score() (Jaccard similarity of bag-of-words) for the 'related:' output. The TSV observations used terms like 'output format', 'tab separated', 'density', 'rendering' — which have LOW Jaccard overlap with ACP observations that use terms like 'action centric', 'projection', 'budget', 'activation'. The two CONCEPT CLUSTERS are semantically synonymous but lexically disjoint. Jaccard similarity is 0 between 'TSV rendering pipeline' and 'Action-Centric Projection' because they share zero keywords despite being about the SAME architectural concern (output formatting). This is SEMANTIC DIVERGENCE (Reconciliation Taxonomy Type 5, Logical) — the same concept expressed in different vocabulary. The fix requires: (1) Semantic similarity (embeddings) instead of lexical (Jaccard). (2) OR: transitivity through shared spec refs — both TSV and ACP reference INV-INTERFACE-001, so they should be connected via the spec graph even when keywords don't overlap. The spec graph IS the shared vocabulary that bridges lexical gaps."
